The paper deals with random subgraphs and their properties, which is a topic in discrete mathematics (cs.DM). It also involves graph theory (cs.GT) and the analysis of algorithms and data structures (cs.DS). The use of randomness and probability suggests that it may also fall under the sub-category of stochastic processes (cs.SI). Finally, the application of the results to communication protocols suggests that it may also be relevant to information theory (cs.IT).
